The code of HexaPDF is now available on [Github](https://github.com/gettalong/hexapdf) and the first
version 0.1.0 can be downloaded from [Rubygems](https://rubygems/gems/hexapdf).

This release provides the basic functionalities for reading and writing PDFs as well as low-level
support for creating PDFs. A command line application for often needed tasks is also available.

Bugs and issues can be reported at HexaPDF's [issue
tracker](https://github.com/gettalong/hexapdf/issues). The
[roadmap](https://github.com/gettalong/hexapdf/wiki/Roadmap-and-Feature-Requests) shows what
features will be implemented next and the Wiki page can also be used to request features.
